This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) as it focuses on developing a neural network for detecting potentially malicious URLs, file paths, named pipes, named mutexes, and registry keys. 

It is also likely to belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it proposes a deep learning approach for feature extraction and classification. 

"cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of machine learning for security purposes. 

"cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a neural network architecture. 

Finally, "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on image or video data, but it does use convolutional neural networks which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
